---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BookLayout from '../../layouts/BookLayout.astro';
import { buildToc } from '../../lib/toc';
import SkinDepthExplorer from '../../components/SkinDepthExplorer.astro';
const toc = buildToc(await getCollection('book'));
---
<BookLayout title="Skin-depth & eddy explorer" toc={toc}>
  <h1>Skin-depth &amp; eddy explorer</h1>
  <p>
    The magnetic skin depth δ = 1/√(πfμσ) (Ch. 6 §6.2) decides which nearby
    materials distort the field and which are transparent. It is the single number
    behind two opposite facts: a conductor with δ ≪ its size hosts eddy currents
    that corrupt the measurement, while the body — non-magnetic and weakly
    conducting — has δ ≈ 7 m at 10 kHz, far larger than itself, so the field
    passes through it almost unperturbed (Ch. 4 §4.2). Sweep the frequency and
    compare materials against the ~0.3 m body reference.
  </p>
  <SkinDepthExplorer />
</BookLayout>
